<a
    href="https://foreignpolicy.com/channel/the-cable/"
    class="department-name">
    <h3 class="department">The Cable</h3></a>
<span
    class="hed-heading"
    href="https://foreignpolicy.com/2009/01/22/posts-bass-to-u-n-as-rice-advisorspeechwriter/">
    <h1 class="hed">Post&#8217;s Bass to U.N. as Rice advisor/speechwriter</h1>
</span>
<h2 class="dek-heading">The Washington Post&#8216;s Al Kamen reports that Warren Bass, the deputy editor of the Post&#8216;s Outlook section and previously a staffer with the 9/11 Commission, has been tapped to be Susan Rice&#8216;s speechwriter and advisor at the United Nations. UPDATE: The Senate voted unanimously to confirm Rice as ambassador to the U.N. Thursday night.</h2>
<div class="meta-data ">
    <address class="author-list">
    <span class="pre">By</span>
    <a
        href="https://foreignpolicy.com/author/laura-rozen/"
        rel="author"
        class="author">
    Laura Rozen</a></address>
    <span class="separator">|</span>
    <time
    pubdate
    datetime="2009-01-22"
    title="January 22nd, 2009"
    class="date-time">
January 22, 2009, 7:12 PM</time>
</div>




				<figure class="figure-image ">
    <!-- Missing image src -->            <!-- No caption found -->
    </figure>


				
			
			
						
			<div class="post-content-main initial-drop-cap shares-position">
				
				
				<p>The <i>Washington Post</i>&#8216;s Al Kamen <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/01/21/AR2009012103687_pf.html">reports </a>that <b>Warren Bass</b>, the deputy editor of the <i>Post</i>&#8216;s Outlook section and previously a staffer with the 9/11 Commission, has been tapped to be <b>Susan Rice</b>&#8216;s speechwriter and advisor at the United Nations. </p>
<p><b>UPDATE: </b>The Senate <a href="http://www.reuters.com/article/rbssFinancialServicesAndRealEstateNews/idUSN2226571320090123">voted</a> unanimously to confirm Rice as ambassador to the U.N. Thursday night.</p>
<div data-fp-lazy-load-image></div>							</div>
			
			
